events.description: Julius Caesar fights Titus Labienus in the Battle of Ruspina.

events.html: • 1762 – Great Britain declares war on Spain, which meant the entry of Spain into the Seven Years' War.[6]

events.description: Constantine Hangerli arrives in Bucharest, Wallachia, as its new Prince, invested by the Ottoman Empire.
events.html: • 1798 – Constantine Hangerli arrives in Bucharest, Wallachia, as its new Prince, invested by the Ottoman Empire.[7]

events.description: The first issue of the Swedish-languaged Saima newspaper founded by J. V. Snellman is published in Kuopio, Finland.

events.description: After having been kidnapped and sold into slavery in the American South, Solomon Northup regains his freedom; his memoir Twelve Years a Slave later becomes a national bestseller.

events.html: • 1854 – The McDonald Islands are discovered by Captain William McDonald aboard the Samarang.[11]

events.description: The New Apostolic Church, a Christian and chiliastic church, is established in Hamburg, Germany.
events.html: • 1863 – The New Apostolic Church, a Christian and chiliastic church, is established in Hamburg, Germany.[12]

events.description: Russo-Turkish War (1877–78): Sofia is liberated from Ottoman rule.
events.html: • 1878 – Russo-Turkish War (1877–78): Sofia is liberated from Ottoman rule.[13]

events.description: The Fabian Society is founded in London, United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1884 – The Fabian Society is founded in London, United Kingdom.[14]

events.description: Sino-French War: French troops under General Oscar de Négrier defeat a numerically superior Qing force at Núi Bop in northern Vietnam.
events.html: • 1885 – Sino-French War: French troops under General Oscar de Négrier defeat a numerically superior Qing force at Núi Bop in northern Vietnam.[15]

events.description: Utah is admitted as the 45th U.S. state.
events.html: • 1896 – Utah is admitted as the 45th U.S. state.[16]

events.description: Topsy, an elephant, is electrocuted by the owners of Luna Park, Coney Island. The Edison film company records the film Electrocuting an Elephant of Topsy's death.

events.description: The Scout Association is incorporated throughout the British Empire by royal charter.
events.html: • 1912 – The Scout Association is incorporated throughout the British Empire by royal charter.[19]

events.description: The Finnish Declaration of Independence is recognized by Russia, Sweden, Germany and France.
events.html: • 1918 – The Finnish Declaration of Independence is recognized by Russia, Sweden, Germany and France.[20]

events.description: World War II: Operation Carpetbagger, involving the dropping of arms and supplies to resistance fighters in Europe, begins.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Operation Carpetbagger, involving the dropping of arms and supplies to resistance fighters in Europe, begins.[21]

events.description: The first day of a three-day “disastrous” tornado outbreak across the south-central United States leaves 41 people dead and at least 412 others injured.

events.description: Burma gains its independence from the United Kingdom, becoming an independent republic.

events.html: • 1956 – The Greek National Radical Union is formed by Konstantinos Karamanlis.[26]

events.description: Luna 1 becomes the first spacecraft to reach the vicinity of the Moon.

events.description: Rose Heilbron becomes the first female judge to sit at the Old Bailey in London, UK.
events.html: • 1972 – Rose Heilbron becomes the first female judge to sit at the Old Bailey in London, UK.[29]

events.description: The Troubles: The Ulster Volunteer Force shoots dead six Irish Catholic civilians in County Armagh, Northern Ireland. The next day, gunmen would shoot dead ten Protestant civilians nearby in retaliation.

events.description: The Maryland train collision: An Amtrak train en route to Boston from Washington, D.C., collides with Conrail engines in Chase, Maryland, United States, killing 16 people.
